{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":521,"text":"We most certainly do talk to terrorists, no question about it."},{"time":5356,"text":"We are at war with a new form of terrorism."},{"time":11242,"text":"It's sort of the good old, traditional form of terrorism,"},{"time":14744,"text":"but it's sort of been packaged for the 21st century."},{"time":18206,"text":"One of the big things about countering terrorism"},{"time":22654,"text":"is, how do you perceive it?"},{"time":25986,"text":"Because perception leads to your response to it."},{"time":29482,"text":"So if you have a traditional perception of terrorism,"},{"time":33710,"text":"it would be that it's one of criminality, one of war."},{"time":37658,"text":"So how are you going to respond to it?"},{"time":39271,"text":"Naturally, it would follow that you meet kind with kind."},{"time":42905,"text":"You fight it. If you have a more modernist approach,"},{"time":46736,"text":"and your perception of terrorism is almost cause-and-effect,"},{"time":50992,"text":"then naturally from that, the responses that come out of it"},{"time":54955,"text":"are much more asymmetrical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58603,"text":"We live in a modern, global world."},{"time":62710,"text":"Terrorists have actually adapted to it."},{"time":66192,"text":"It's something we have to, too, and that means the people"},{"time":69941,"text":"who are working on counterterrorism responses"},{"time":73081,"text":"have to start, in effect, putting on"},{"time":75905,"text":"their Google-tinted glasses, or whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80159,"text":"For my part, what I wanted us to do was just to look at"},{"time":84952,"text":"terrorism as though it was a global brand,"},{"time":88456,"text":"say, Coca-Cola."},{"time":90085,"text":"Both are fairly bad for your health. (Laughter)"},{"time":96102,"text":"If you look at it as a brand in those ways,"},{"time":100132,"text":"what you'll come to realize is, it's a pretty flawed product."},{"time":103396,"text":"As we've said, it's pretty bad for your health,"},{"time":106489,"text":"it's bad for those who it affects,"},{"time":108495,"text":"and it's not actually good if you're a suicide bomber either."},{"time":111528,"text":"It doesn't actually do what it says on the tin."},{"time":115144,"text":"You're not really going to get 72 virgins in heaven."},{"time":120136,"text":"It's not going to happen, I don't think."},{"time":122606,"text":"And you're not really going to, in the '80s, end capitalism"},{"time":126584,"text":"by supporting one of these groups. It's a load of nonsense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129505,"text":"But what you realize, it's got an Achilles' heel."},{"time":132783,"text":"The brand has an Achilles' heel."},{"time":135536,"text":"We've mentioned the health,"},{"time":137303,"text":"but it needs consumers to buy into it."},{"time":140983,"text":"The consumers it needs are the terrorist constituency."},{"time":145063,"text":"They're the people who buy into the brand, support them,"},{"time":147764,"text":"facilitate them, and they're the people"},{"time":151072,"text":"we've got to reach out to."},{"time":153587,"text":"We've got to attack that brand in front of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156447,"text":"There's two essential ways of doing that, if we carry on this brand theme."},{"time":160700,"text":"One is reducing their market. What I mean is,"},{"time":163978,"text":"it's their brand against our brand. We've got to compete."},{"time":168754,"text":"We've got to show we're a better product."},{"time":171006,"text":"If I'm trying to show we're a better product,"},{"time":174163,"text":"I probably wouldn't do things like Guantanamo Bay."},{"time":179094,"text":"We've talked there about curtailing the underlying need"},{"time":182759,"text":"for the product itself. You could be looking there at"},{"time":186407,"text":"poverty, injustice, all those sorts of things"},{"time":189992,"text":"which feed terrorism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191521,"text":"The other thing to do is to knock the product,"},{"time":195253,"text":"attack the brand myth, as we've said."},{"time":197448,"text":"You know, there's nothing heroic about killing a young kid."},{"time":200807,"text":"Perhaps we need to focus on that and get that message back across."},{"time":205503,"text":"We've got to reveal the dangers in the product."},{"time":208597,"text":"Our target audience, it's not just the producers of terrorism,"},{"time":212246,"text":"as I've said, the terrorists."},{"time":213447,"text":"It's not just the marketeers of terrorism,"},{"time":215834,"text":"which is those who finance, those who facilitate it,"},{"time":220641,"text":"but it's the consumers of terrorism."},{"time":222554,"text":"We've got to get in to those homelands."},{"time":225788,"text":"That's where they recruit from. That's where they get their power and strength."},{"time":229257,"text":"That's where their consumers come from."},{"time":231609,"text":"And we have to get our messaging in there."},{"time":235521,"text":"So the essentials are, we've got to have interaction"},{"time":239370,"text":"in those areas, with the terrorists, the facilitators, etc."},{"time":242713,"text":"We've got to engage, we've got to educate,"},{"time":245848,"text":"and we've got to have dialogue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248651,"text":"Now, staying on this brand thing for just a few more seconds,"},{"time":252802,"text":"think about delivery mechanisms."},{"time":256054,"text":"How are we going to do these attacks?"},{"time":257687,"text":"Well, reducing the market is really one for governments"},{"time":260696,"text":"and civil society. We've got to show we're better."},{"time":264214,"text":"We've got to show our values."},{"time":268056,"text":"We've got to practice what we preach."},{"time":270358,"text":"But when it comes to knocking the brand,"},{"time":272571,"text":"if the terrorists are Coca-Cola and we're Pepsi,"},{"time":277043,"text":"I don't think, being Pepsi, anything we say about Coca-Cola,"},{"time":281057,"text":"anyone's going to believe us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282939,"text":"So we've got to find a different mechanism,"},{"time":285264,"text":"and one of the best mechanisms I've ever come across"},{"time":287656,"text":"is the victims of terrorism."},{"time":290313,"text":"They are somebody who can actually stand there and say,"},{"time":293226,"text":"\"This product's crap. I had it and I was sick for days."},{"time":297654,"text":"It burnt my hand, whatever.\" You believe them."},{"time":301100,"text":"You can see their scars. You trust them."},{"time":303743,"text":"But whether it's victims, whether it's governments,"},{"time":309008,"text":"NGOs, or even the Queen yesterday, in Northern Ireland,"},{"time":314713,"text":"we have to interact and engage with those different"},{"time":318815,"text":"layers of terrorism, and, in effect,"},{"time":323410,"text":"we do have to have a little dance with the devil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327457,"text":"This is my favorite part of my speech."},{"time":330440,"text":"I wanted to blow you all up to try and make a point,"},{"time":333696,"text":"but — (Laughter) —"},{"time":337418,"text":"TED, for health and safety reasons, have told me"},{"time":340206,"text":"I've got to do a countdown, so"},{"time":341712,"text":"I feel like a bit of an Irish or Jewish terrorist,"},{"time":345010,"text":"sort of a health and safety terrorist, and I — (Laughter) —"},{"time":350424,"text":"I've got to count 3, 2, 1, and"},{"time":353733,"text":"it's a bit alarming, so thinking of what my motto would be,"},{"time":357060,"text":"and it would be, \"Body parts, not heart attacks.\""},{"time":359818,"text":"So 3, 2, 1. (Explosion sound)"},{"time":365309,"text":"Very good. (Laughter)"},{"time":370256,"text":"Now, lady in 15J was a suicide bomber amongst us all."},{"time":378065,"text":"We're all victims of terrorism."},{"time":380190,"text":"There's 625 of us in this room. We're going to be scarred for life."},{"time":385091,"text":"There was a father and a son who sat in that seat over there."},{"time":389166,"text":"The son's dead. The father lives."},{"time":391650,"text":"The father will probably kick himself for years to come"},{"time":397571,"text":"that he didn't take that seat instead of his kid."},{"time":401810,"text":"He's going to take to alcohol, and he's probably"},{"time":403823,"text":"going to kill himself in three years. That's the stats."},{"time":408183,"text":"There's a very young, attractive lady over here,"},{"time":411927,"text":"and she has something which I think's the worst form"},{"time":414955,"text":"of psychological, physical injury I've ever seen"},{"time":417751,"text":"out of a suicide bombing: It's human shrapnel."},{"time":421447,"text":"What it means is, when she sat in a restaurant"},{"time":423600,"text":"in years to come, 10 years to come, 15 years to come,"},{"time":426605,"text":"or she's on the beach, every so often she's going to start"},{"time":429087,"text":"rubbing her skin, and out of there will come"},{"time":432060,"text":"a piece of that shrapnel."},{"time":434294,"text":"And that is a hard thing for the head to take."},{"time":439526,"text":"There's a lady over there as well who lost her legs"},{"time":442454,"text":"in this bombing."},{"time":445966,"text":"She's going to find out that she gets a pitiful amount"},{"time":450050,"text":"of money off our government"},{"time":454157,"text":"for looking after what's happened to her."},{"time":457449,"text":"She had a daughter who was going to go to one of the best"},{"time":459589,"text":"universities. She's going to give up university"},{"time":462290,"text":"to look after Mum."},{"time":466019,"text":"We're all here, and all of those who watch it"},{"time":468551,"text":"are going to be traumatized by this event,"},{"time":471190,"text":"but all of you here who are victims are going to learn"},{"time":474338,"text":"some hard truths."},{"time":475920,"text":"That is, our society, we sympathize, but after a while,"},{"time":480641,"text":"we start to ignore. We don't do enough as a society."},{"time":484529,"text":"We do not look after our victims, and we do not enable them,"},{"time":488106,"text":"and what I'm going to try and show is that actually,"},{"time":491114,"text":"victims are the best weapon we have"},{"time":493898,"text":"against more terrorism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497074,"text":"How would the government at the turn of the millennium"},{"time":501290,"text":"approach today? Well, we all know."},{"time":503515,"text":"What they'd have done then is an invasion."},{"time":506119,"text":"If the suicide bomber was from Wales,"},{"time":509297,"text":"good luck to Wales, I'd say."},{"time":511642,"text":"Knee-jerk legislation, emergency provision legislation --"},{"time":515394,"text":"which hits at the very basis of our society, as we all know --"},{"time":519093,"text":"it's a mistake."},{"time":522266,"text":"We're going to drive prejudice throughout Edinburgh,"},{"time":525721,"text":"throughout the U.K., for Welsh people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530151,"text":"Today's approach, governments have learned from their mistakes."},{"time":535796,"text":"They are looking at what I've started off on,"},{"time":538034,"text":"on these more asymmetrical approaches to it,"},{"time":541588,"text":"more modernist views, cause and effect."},{"time":544290,"text":"But mistakes of the past are inevitable."},{"time":547067,"text":"It's human nature."},{"time":548567,"text":"The fear and the pressure to do something on them"},{"time":552303,"text":"is going to be immense. They are going to make mistakes."},{"time":554583,"text":"They're not just going to be smart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558228,"text":"There was a famous Irish terrorist who once summed up"},{"time":561542,"text":"the point very beautifully. He said,"},{"time":564597,"text":"\"The thing is, about the British government, is, is that it's got"},{"time":566709,"text":"to be lucky all the time, and we only have to be lucky once.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":571173,"text":"So what we need to do is we have to effect it."},{"time":574413,"text":"We've got to start thinking about being more proactive."},{"time":577169,"text":"We need to build an arsenal of noncombative weapons"},{"time":581857,"text":"in this war on terrorism."},{"time":583478,"text":"But of course, it's ideas -- is not something that governments do very well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591926,"text":"I want to go back just to before the bang, to this idea of"},{"time":596105,"text":"brand, and I was talking about Coke and Pepsi, etc."},{"time":600299,"text":"We see it as terrorism versus democracy in that brand war."},{"time":604210,"text":"They'll see it as freedom fighters and truth"},{"time":606231,"text":"against injustice, imperialism, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613454,"text":"We do have to see this as a deadly battlefield."},{"time":617445,"text":"It's not just [our] flesh and blood they want."},{"time":620619,"text":"They actually want our cultural souls, and that's why"},{"time":623492,"text":"the brand analogy is a very interesting way of looking at this."},{"time":627503,"text":"If we look at al Qaeda. Al Qaeda was essentially"},{"time":632083,"text":"a product on a shelf in a souk somewhere"},{"time":636623,"text":"which not many people had heard of."},{"time":638762,"text":"9/11 launched it. It was its big marketing day,"},{"time":642926,"text":"and it was packaged for the 21st century. They knew what they were doing."},{"time":647795,"text":"They were effectively [doing] something in this brand image"},{"time":651723,"text":"of creating a brand which can be franchised around"},{"time":654907,"text":"the world, where there's poverty, ignorance and injustice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660567,"text":"We, as I've said, have got to hit that market,"},{"time":664630,"text":"but we've got to use our heads rather than our might."},{"time":668089,"text":"If we perceive it in this way as a brand, or other ways of thinking at it like this,"},{"time":671863,"text":"we will not resolve or counter terrorism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676302,"text":"What I'd like to do is just briefly go through a few examples"},{"time":679662,"text":"from my work on areas where we try and approach these things differently."},{"time":685093,"text":"The first one has been dubbed \"lawfare,\""},{"time":688782,"text":"for want of a better word."},{"time":691224,"text":"When we originally looked at bringing civil actions against terrorists,"},{"time":695424,"text":"everyone thought we were a bit mad and mavericks"},{"time":697790,"text":"and crackpots. Now it's got a title. Everyone's doing it."},{"time":701554,"text":"There's a bomb, people start suing."},{"time":703167,"text":"But one of the first early cases on this was the Omagh Bombing."},{"time":706858,"text":"A civil action was brought from 1998."},{"time":710597,"text":"In Omagh, bomb went off, Real IRA,"},{"time":714005,"text":"middle of a peace process."},{"time":716220,"text":"That meant that the culprits couldn't really be prosecuted"},{"time":720363,"text":"for lots of reasons, mostly to do with the peace process"},{"time":723611,"text":"and what was going on, the greater good."},{"time":725828,"text":"It also meant, then, if you can imagine this,"},{"time":728323,"text":"that the people who bombed your children"},{"time":730626,"text":"and your husbands were walking around the supermarket"},{"time":735983,"text":"that you lived in."},{"time":737667,"text":"Some of those victims said enough is enough."},{"time":741429,"text":"We brought a private action, and thank God, 10 years later,"},{"time":744863,"text":"we actually won it. There is a slight appeal on"},{"time":747458,"text":"at the moment so I have to be a bit careful,"},{"time":749273,"text":"but I'm fairly confident."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751390,"text":"Why was it effective?"},{"time":753009,"text":"It was effective not just because justice was seen to be done"},{"time":755646,"text":"where there was a huge void."},{"time":757385,"text":"It was because the Real IRA and other terrorist groups,"},{"time":762011,"text":"their whole strength is from the fact that they are"},{"time":764090,"text":"an underdog. When we put the victims as the underdog"},{"time":768836,"text":"and flipped it, they didn't know what to do."},{"time":771976,"text":"They were embarrassed. Their recruitment went down."},{"time":776227,"text":"The bombs actually stopped -- fact -- because of this action."},{"time":780515,"text":"We became, or those victims became, more importantly,"},{"time":784220,"text":"a ghost that haunted the terrorist organization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788196,"text":"There's other examples. We have a case called Almog"},{"time":790995,"text":"which is to do with a bank that was,"},{"time":795187,"text":"allegedly, from our point of view,"},{"time":798193,"text":"giving rewards to suicide bombers."},{"time":802108,"text":"Just by bringing the very action,"},{"time":805116,"text":"that bank has stopped doing it, and indeed,"},{"time":807627,"text":"the powers that be around the world, which for real politic"},{"time":810031,"text":"reasons before, couldn't actually deal with this issue,"},{"time":813374,"text":"because there was lots of competing interests,"},{"time":814904,"text":"have actually closed down those loopholes in the banking system."},{"time":817888,"text":"There's another case called the McDonald case,"},{"time":820603,"text":"where some victims of Semtex, of the Provisional IRA bombings,"},{"time":824925,"text":"which were supplied by Gaddafi, sued,"},{"time":831544,"text":"and that action has led to amazing things for new Libya."},{"time":836481,"text":"New Libya has been compassionate towards those victims,"},{"time":839434,"text":"and started taking it -- so it started a whole new dialogue there."},{"time":843066,"text":"But the problem is, we need more and more support"},{"time":847349,"text":"for these ideas and cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850151,"text":"Civil affairs and civil society initiatives."},{"time":854577,"text":"A good one is in Somalia. There's a war on piracy."},{"time":857104,"text":"If anyone thinks you can have a war on piracy"},{"time":858910,"text":"like a war on terrorism and beat it, you're wrong."},{"time":861536,"text":"What we're trying to do there is turn pirates to fisherman."},{"time":864523,"text":"They used to be fisherman, of course,"},{"time":866747,"text":"but we stole their fish and dumped a load of toxic waste"},{"time":869943,"text":"in their water, so what we're trying to do is create"},{"time":873238,"text":"security and employment by bringing a coastguard"},{"time":875724,"text":"along with the fisheries industry, and I can guarantee you,"},{"time":879061,"text":"as that builds, al Shabaab and such likes will not have"},{"time":881925,"text":"the poverty and injustice any longer to prey on those people."},{"time":885749,"text":"These initiatives cost less than a missile,"},{"time":889624,"text":"and certainly less than any soldier's life,"},{"time":892591,"text":"but more importantly, it takes the war to their homelands,"},{"time":895446,"text":"and not onto our shore,"},{"time":897744,"text":"and we're looking at the causes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899188,"text":"The last one I wanted to talk about was dialogue."},{"time":902637,"text":"The advantages of dialogue are obvious."},{"time":905443,"text":"It self-educates both sides, enables a better understanding,"},{"time":909745,"text":"reveals the strengths and weaknesses,"},{"time":911967,"text":"and yes, like some of the speakers before,"},{"time":914568,"text":"the shared vulnerability does lead to trust, and"},{"time":918457,"text":"it does then become, that process, part of normalization."},{"time":921362,"text":"But it's not an easy road. After the bomb,"},{"time":926035,"text":"the victims are not into this."},{"time":929164,"text":"There's practical problems."},{"time":931058,"text":"It's politically risky for the protagonists"},{"time":933954,"text":"and for the interlocutors. On one occasion"},{"time":936689,"text":"I was doing it, every time I did a point that they didn't like,"},{"time":939130,"text":"they actually threw stones at me,"},{"time":940991,"text":"and when I did a point they liked,"},{"time":942978,"text":"they starting shooting in the air, equally not great. (Laughter)"},{"time":947573,"text":"Whatever the point, it gets to the heart of the problem,"},{"time":950775,"text":"you're doing it, you're talking to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952891,"text":"Now, I just want to end with saying, if we follow reason,"},{"time":956634,"text":"we realize that I think we'd all say that we want to"},{"time":961996,"text":"have a perception of terrorism which is not just a pure"},{"time":964678,"text":"military perception of it."},{"time":968446,"text":"We need to foster more"},{"time":970903,"text":"modern and asymmetrical responses to it."},{"time":973688,"text":"This isn't about being soft on terrorism."},{"time":976243,"text":"It's about fighting them on contemporary battlefields."},{"time":979963,"text":"We must foster innovation, as I've said."},{"time":982914,"text":"Governments are receptive. It won't come from those dusty corridors."},{"time":986786,"text":"The private sector has a role."},{"time":988999,"text":"The role we could do right now is going away"},{"time":991572,"text":"and looking at how we can support victims around the world"},{"time":995297,"text":"to bring initiatives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996769,"text":"If I was to leave you with some big questions here which"},{"time":999572,"text":"may change one's perception to it, and who knows what"},{"time":1003047,"text":"thoughts and responses will come out of it,"},{"time":1005426,"text":"but did myself and my terrorist group actually need"},{"time":1009381,"text":"to blow you up to make our point?"},{"time":1012617,"text":"We have to ask ourselves these questions, however unpalatable."},{"time":1016999,"text":"Have we been ignoring an injustice or a humanitarian"},{"time":1020133,"text":"struggle somewhere in the world?"},{"time":1022898,"text":"What if, actually, engagement on poverty and injustice"},{"time":1025548,"text":"is exactly what the terrorists wanted us to do?"},{"time":1027963,"text":"What if the bombs are just simply wake-up calls for us?"},{"time":1031068,"text":"What happens if that bomb went off"},{"time":1034267,"text":"because we didn't have any thoughts and things in place"},{"time":1037574,"text":"to allow dialogue to deal with these things and interaction?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042253,"text":"What is definitely uncontroversial"},{"time":1045420,"text":"is that, as I've said, we've got to stop being reactive,"},{"time":1047227,"text":"and more proactive, and I just want to leave you"},{"time":1050844,"text":"with one idea, which is that"},{"time":1054252,"text":"it's a provocative question for you to think about,"},{"time":1057412,"text":"and the answer will require sympathy with the devil."},{"time":1061533,"text":"It's a question that's been tackled by many great thinkers"},{"time":1064250,"text":"and writers: What if society actually needs crisis to change?"},{"time":1069167,"text":"What if society actually needs terrorism"},{"time":1073470,"text":"to change and adapt for the better?"},{"time":1075013,"text":"It's those Bulgakov themes, it's that picture of Jesus"},{"time":1079564,"text":"and the Devil hand in hand in Gethsemane"},{"time":1082768,"text":"walking into the moonlight."},{"time":1085048,"text":"What it would mean is that humans,"},{"time":1087896,"text":"in order to survive in development,"},{"time":1090552,"text":"quite Darwinian spirit here,"},{"time":1092627,"text":"inherently must dance with the devil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1096957,"text":"A lot of people say that communism was defeated"},{"time":1101216,"text":"by the Rolling Stones. It's a good theory."},{"time":1105210,"text":"Maybe the Rolling Stones has a place in this."},{"time":1108046,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1110633,"text":"(Music) (Applause)"},{"time":1119503,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}